FBIS4-64554 "drweu087aa_94002" FBIS-WEU-94-087 Daily Report 3 May 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS International Press Institute Sets Up Russian Committee International Press Institute Sets Up Russian Committee AU0305173594 Paris AFP in English 1606 GMT 3 May 94 AU0305173594 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Vienna, May 3 (AFP) -- The International Press Institute [IPI], made up of journalists from 85 countries fighting for freedom of the press, Tuesday [3 May] set up an IPI Russian Committee, a statement from the organisation said. The IPI said Russian media faced serious economic and administrative problems as well as a poor distribution system. The new IPI cell in Russia will report back to the central secretariat on the free flow of information and on general developments in the media.
